comments.body:
The thing is, I have already renamed the comment itself to remain internally consistent with the code. Before the merger the code looked like this:
```
// Calls to this should probably be changed to expectThrows.
// This was added as it was all over the place in the pre
// JUnit code.
object ThrowsHelper {
  def assertThrowsAnd[T <: Throwable, U](
      expectedThrowable: Class[T],
      code: => U)(cond: T => Boolean): Unit = {
    val c = cond(expectThrows(expectedThrowable, code))
    assert(c)
  }
}
``` 
Now that you mention it, I am not sure what this comment really means - I assumed it wanted the calls to this object to be changed, but maybe it meant just the function name (as in `expectThrowsAnd`). Perhaps it should be removed either way for the ambiguity.

